1️⃣ Multiple Category Filter kya hota hai

Abhi tumhare code me category checkbox hai:

<input type="checkbox" name="category" value="{{ $category->id }}">

Iska problem ye hai ki sirf ek category hi filter hoti hai.

Example:

User select kare:

✔ Shoes
✔ T-Shirt
✔ Jackets

To user chahta hai teeno category ke products ek saath show ho.

🔹 Multiple category kaise kaam karta hai

User select kare:

Category Selected	Result
Shoes	sirf shoes
Shoes + Shirts	shoes aur shirts
Shoes + Shirts + Jackets	teeno
🔹 Iske liye filter input change karna padta hai
<input type="checkbox" name="category[]" value="{{ $category->id }}">

Notice:

category[]

Isse array send hoti hai controller me.

Example request:

category = [1,3,5]
🔹 Controller me filter
if($request->category){
    $query->whereIn('category_id',$request->category);
}

whereIn ka matlab:

category_id IN (1,3,5)
2️⃣ AJAX Pagination kya hota hai

Pagination matlab:

Agar tumhare paas

100 products

ho to ek page pe sab show nahi karte.

Example:

Page	Products
Page 1	1-10
Page 2	11-20
Page 3	21-30
🔹 Normal Pagination

Laravel me:

$products = Product::paginate(10);

Page reload hota hai.

🔹 AJAX Pagination

Page reload nahi hota.

User Next Page click kare:

Page change → products load → page reload nahi

Sirf product grid update hota hai.

Exactly Amazon jaisa.

3️⃣ AJAX Pagination ka flow
Step 1 Controller
$products = $query->paginate(10);
Step 2 Blade
<div id="product-list">
    @include('partials.products')
</div>

Pagination:

{{ $products->links() }}
Step 3 AJAX
$(document).on('click','.pagination a',function(e){

    e.preventDefault();

    let url = $(this).attr('href');

    $.get(url,function(data){
        $('#product-list').html(data);
    });

});
4️⃣ AJAX pagination ka benefit
Normal	AJAX
page reload	page reload nahi
slow	fast
UX weak	UX strong
